 SURVEYS-A SERVICE TO SUBSCRIBERS.THE CANADIAN PERIODICAL INDEX (CPI) BEGAN AS AN INDEXING SERVICE AT THEWINDSOR PUBLIC LIBRARY WHERE, FROM 1924-32 MIMEOGRAPHED PERIODICAL INDEXESWERE PRODUCED. TODAY IT IS ORGANISED BY THE CANADIAN LIBRARY ASSOCIATION,WHICH ASSUMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR IT IN 1946. EVERY 3 YEARS CLA ESTABLISHES NEWRATES BY MEANS OF A SUBSCRIPTION RATE SURVEY. A QUESTIONNAIRE IS SENT TO ALLSUBSCRIBERS, LISTING PERIODICALS COVERED BY CPI, AND ASKING SUBSCRIBERS TOLIST WHICH OF THESE ARE INCLUDED IN THE INSTITUTION'S HOLDINGS. COST-PER-ENTRYIS THEN ESTABLISHED, AND TOTAL ENTRIES FOR A YEAR IN CPI ARE CALCULATED.TAKING COSTS OF SALARIES, AUTOMATION, PUBLISHING AND RENT, CPI'S BUDGET ISESTABLISHED. DISCUSSES THE SURVEY IN DETAIL AND OTHER CONSIDERATIONS WHICHARISE FROM IT